Thousands of John Lennon fans, some

"It's a great day, isn't it?"
Lennon's widow, Yoko Ono, asked the crowd.
"I think John would be happy, too."
Cyndi Lauper, in a white minidress, sang "Hey Bulldog," and Dave Edmunds, backed by the Royal Liverpool Philharmonic Orchestra, did the Beatles classic, "A Day in the Life."
His version of "All You Need is Love," turned into a singalong with the crowd, and Kylie Minogue did "Help."
Lennon was slain on Dec. 8, 1980, when he was 40.
